<p>Born in 1946 as Farrokh Bulsara in Zanzibar, he attended English-style boarding schools in India from the age of eight and returned to Zanzibar after secondary school. In 1964, his family fled the Zanzibar Revolution, moving to Middlesex, England, where he started working part-time at Heathrow airport. </p>
